
[1]windlas

   WINDLAS, WINDLASS, n. [wind and lace.]

   1. A machine for raising great weights, consisting of a cylinder or
   roller of timber, moving on its axis and turned by levers, with a rope
   or chain attached to the weight.

   2. A handle by which any thing is turned. [Not in use.]
